<db:titleabbrev>Qt Quick Controls Reference Documentation</db:titleabbrev>
<db:abstract>
<db:para>Provides a set of UI controls for Qt Quick.</db:para>
</db:abstract>
<db:pubdate>2024-12-27</db:pubdate>
<db:date>2024-12-27</db:date>
<db:authorgroup>
<db:author>
<db:orgname class="corporation">The Qt Company Ltd.</db:orgname>
</db:author>
</db:authorgroup>
</db:info>
<db:para>Qt Quick Controls provides a set of controls that can be used to build complete interfaces in Qt Quick. The module was introduced in Qt 5.7.</db:para>
<db:mediaobject>
<db:imageobject>
<db:imagedata fileref="images/qtquickcontrols2-styles.png"/>
</db:imageobject>
</db:mediaobject>
<db:para>Qt Quick Controls comes with a selection customizable styles. See <db:link xlink:href="qtquickcontrols2-styles.xml">Styling Qt Quick Controls</db:link> for more details.</db:para>
<db:section xml:id="prerequisites">
<db:title>Prerequisites</db:title>
<db:para>The <db:link xlink:href="qtquick-controls2-qmlmodule.xml">QML types</db:link> can be imported into your application using the following import statement in your <db:code>.qml</db:code> file:</db:para>
<db:programlisting language="qml">import QtQuick.Controls 2.15
</db:programlisting>
<db:para>The <db:link xlink:href="qtquickcontrols2-module.xml">C++ classes</db:link> can be included into your application using the following include statement:</db:para>
<db:programlisting language="cpp">#include &amp;lt;QtQuickControls2&amp;gt;
</db:programlisting>
<db:para>To link against the corresponding C++ libraries, add the following to your qmake project file:</db:para>
<db:programlisting language="cpp">QT += quickcontrols2
</db:programlisting>
<db:para>For more details, see <db:link xlink:href="qtquickcontrols2-gettingstarted.xml">Getting Started with Qt Quick Controls</db:link>.</db:para>
<db:section xml:id="building-from-source">
<db:title>Building From Source</db:title>
<db:para>When building from source, ensure that the <db:link xlink:href="qtgraphicaleffects-index.xml">Qt Graphical Effects</db:link> module is also built, as Qt Quick Controls requires it.</db:para>
<db:para>The <db:link xlink:href="license-changes.xml#qt-image-formats">Qt Image Formats</db:link> module is recommended, but not required. It provides support for the <db:code>.webp</db:code> format used by the <db:link xlink:href="qtquickcontrols2-imagine.xml#animated-images">Imagine style</db:link>.</db:para>
</db:section>
</db:section>
<db:section xml:id="versions">
<db:title>Versions</db:title>
<db:para>Qt Quick Controls.0 was introduced in Qt 5.7. Subsequent minor Qt releases increment the import version of the Qt Quick Controls modules by one, until Qt 5.12, where the import versions match Qt's minor version. The experimental Qt Labs modules use import version 1.0.</db:para>
